translated: Björkö, Jönköping County, 1st district, son of estate owner Ivar B. and Kate Wetche. Married in 1924 to Astrid Nordenanker. Children: Anna-Lisa (born 1925), Iwar (born 1927), Monica (born 1931), Johan (born 1934). Completed high school in 1915, officer training in 1917, and agricultural school in 1919. Became a second lieutenant in Småland's hussar regiment in 1918, first lieutenant in 1920, and captain in the Life Hussar Regiment in 1923. Resigned in 1932. Owned the estates of Rödjenäs and Sjöeryd. Chairman of the Björkö municipal council from 1934, of the Jönköping 1st household society, and of the Jönköping 1st forestry committee from 1935. Board member of the Småland and other provincial mortgage societies from 1939, and member of the board of the Swedish general mortgage bank from 1942. Appointed by the King as a board member of the Växjö diocese and holding various positions of public trust. Awarded RVO (Knight of the Order of Vasa), LLA (Knight of the Order of the Sword), and GM (Medal of the Order of the Household).
